AERION‑Ω — ABSTRACTION ENGINE

Omricon Abstraction Core — Rev Ω.1

---

1. Purpose

AERION‑Ω is the deterministic abstraction engine of the Omricon Trilogy Core.

Its function is to convert SERA‑Ω’s structured representation into a compressed, meaning‑preserving, fully traceable abstract representation.

AERION performs:
• compression
• redundancy removal
• pattern collapse
• structural simplification
• traceability mapping
• conflict surfacing

AERION does not:
• interpret
• infer
• guess
• rewrite
• reorder logic
• change meaning

---

2. Position in the Pipeline

SERA‑Ω → AERION‑Ω → Domain Modules → Ω‑Core

AERION is the bridge between structure and domain reasoning.

---

3. Input Contract (From SERA‑Ω)

AERION‑Ω accepts:
• structured_representation
• structure_type
• structural_constraints
• conflict_flags
• ambiguity_flags
• structural_confidence = 1.0
• lineage → VORIN payload reference

AERION must not reinterpret or modify these.

---

4. Output Contract (To Domain Modules)

AERION‑Ω outputs:

ABSTRACT_REPRESENTATION
• units: list of ABSTRACT_UNIT
• traceability_map: AU_ID → list of SERA node IDs
• abstraction_conflict_flags
• uncertainty_flags
• metadata

This is the only payload Domain Modules may consume.

---

5. AERION‑Ω Invariants

AERION must never:
• invent meaning
• remove essential meaning
• change intent or tone
• reorder in a way that alters logic or causality
• break traceability
• hide conflicts or ambiguity
• override SERA constraints
• violate Ω‑Core invariants

AERION must always:
• preserve meaning
• preserve order
• preserve logic
• surface abstraction conflicts
• maintain total traceability
• operate deterministically
• be invariant‑safe and governor‑safe

---

6. AERION‑Ω Roadway Stages

Stage 1 — Intake and Validation
• Validate SERA output
• If STRUCTURE_CONFLICT or STRUCTURE_COLLAPSE → stop and defer to Ω‑Core

Stage 2 — Scope Selection
• Select whole structure, subtree, or segment
• Respect structural_constraints and governor limits

Stage 3 — Compression Engine
• Apply deterministic compression rules
• merge_equivalent
• collapse_pattern
• remove_redundancy
• structural_simplification

Stage 4 — Traceability Mapping
• Build traceability_map
• Ensure no abstract unit is unbacked

Stage 5 — Conflict and Uncertainty Detection
• Set abstraction_conflict_flags
• Set uncertainty_flags

Stage 6 — Output Assembly
• Emit ABSTRACT_REPRESENTATION
• Hand off to Ω‑Core

