7. Abstract Unit Schema

ABSTRACT_UNIT
• id: deterministic string
• type: concept, step, argument, condition, action, relation, cluster
• content: compressed meaning
• source_nodes: list of SERA node IDs
• lineage:
– sera_nodes
– vorin_fields (AREA, PROBLEM, REQUEST, DOMAIN)
• order_index: integer
• logical_role: premise, conclusion, step, modifier, qualifier, none
• abstraction_level: low, medium, high
• compression_method: merge_equivalent, collapse_pattern, remove_redundancy, structural_simplification
• conflict_flags
• uncertainty_flags
• metadata

Hard constraints:
• source_nodes must be non‑empty
• order_index must preserve SERA order
• content must not add or remove essential meaning
• lineage must allow full reconstruction back to SERA and VORIN

---

8. Abstract Representation Schema

ABSTRACT_REPRESENTATION
• units: list of ABSTRACT_UNIT
• traceability_map: AU_ID → list of SERA node IDs
• abstraction_conflict_flags
• uncertainty_flags
• metadata

