9. AERION‑Ω Compression Rules

All rules must be deterministic, reversible at the structural level, invariant‑safe, and traceability‑preserving.

If a rule would violate invariants, it must not apply and must raise a conflict flag.

---

Rule 1 — merge_equivalent

Purpose:
Merge structurally and semantically equivalent nodes.

Preconditions:
• identical content
• identical logical role
• identical parent
• identical order
• no conflicts

Operation:
• create one abstract unit
• type = concept or cluster
• source_nodes = union of all nodes
• order_index = first node

Failure:
• if equivalence is ambiguous → MEANING_LOSS

---

Rule 2 — collapse_pattern

Purpose:
Compress repeated structural patterns.

Preconditions:
• repeated substructures
• identical structure type
• identical ordering pattern

Operation:
• create one abstract unit describing the pattern

Failure:
• if pattern detection requires inference → STRUCTURAL_DEPENDENCY_LOSS

---

Rule 3 — remove_redundancy

Purpose:
Remove nodes that add no new meaning.

Preconditions:
• strict restatement
• no unique constraints
• no dependency loss

Operation:
• fold redundant node IDs into an existing abstract unit

Failure:
• if redundancy is not provable → MEANING_LOSS

---

Rule 4 — structural_simplification

Purpose:
Flatten overly nested structures without altering logic.

Preconditions:
• nesting exceeds safe threshold
• flattening preserves logic and order

Operation:
• create simplified abstract units representing the same logic

Failure:
• if flattening hides a branch → STRUCTURAL_DEPENDENCY_LOSS

---

10. Failure Modes

• ABSTRACTION_CONFLICT — safe abstraction impossible
• ABSTRACTION_UNSAFE — traceability cannot be preserved
• ABSTRACTION_OVERLOAD — structure too dense to compress safely
• ABSTRACTION_COLLAPSE — no valid abstraction exists

Each failure must include:
• reason
• flags
• location
• suggested fallback

---

11. Determinism Requirements

AERION‑Ω must be:
• deterministic
• reproducible
• invariant‑safe
• governor‑safe
• SERA‑aligned
• VORIN‑traceable

Same structure → same abstraction → every time.

No randomness.
No heuristics.
No probabilistic behaviour.

